<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1904-07-16T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1904-07-16T00:00:00-05:00" n="861" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d861">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Loomis</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Leishman</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1904-07-16"><hi rend="italic">July 16,
                                1904</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>(Mr. Loomis instructs Mr. Leishman to ask an Imperial audience at a fixed
                            day and hour in the near future, and to state to the minister for
                            foreign affairs that the Government of the United States fails to
                            understand the delay in according him the treatment due to the friendly
                            relations of the two countries.)</p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>